<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Described from Java on sugar cane, and widely distributed in Asia, this is the only 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Podothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Podothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Podothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from China that is uniformly brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 17–22" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 17 - 22. Podothrips adult colour patterns 17 P. lucasseni 18 P. odonaspicola 19 P. semiflavus 20 P. femoralis sp. nov. 21 P. sasacola. Some important features of femoralis sp. nov. 22 mesopresternum and metathoracic sternopleural sutures. Scale bars: 200 microns." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/349333" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.882.39029.figures17-22">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. hawaiiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. hawaiiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Hawaii and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. oryzae" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="oryzae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. oryzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Thailand were placed as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. lucasseni" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="lucasseni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">P. lucasseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1975.tb00135.x" author="Ritchie, JM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomology (B)" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" pagination="261 - 282" refId="B14" refString="Ritchie, JM, 1974. A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae. Journal of Entomology (B) 43: 261 - 282" title="A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1975.tb00135.x" volume="43" year="1974">Ritchie (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. This species was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Okajima, S" journalOrPublisher="Kontyu" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" pagination="713 - 718" refId="B12" refString="Okajima, S, 1986. Studies on the genus Podothrips Hood from Taiwan, with description of a new species (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripidae). Kontyu 54: 713 - 718" title="Studies on the genus Podothrips Hood from Taiwan, with description of a new species (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripidae)." volume="54" year="1986">Okajima (1986)</bibRefCitation>
from China (Taiwan), and a female and a male from Guizhou Province have been examined here.
</paragraph>
